<DocsLayout title="Desktop App">
  <h1>Desktop App</h1>
  <p>
    claustre includes a native macOS desktop application built with
    <a href="https://tauri.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tauri v2</a>.
    It provides the same project and task management features as the TUI in a
    windowed GUI, sharing the same SQLite database and library code.
  </p>

  <h2>Launching</h2>
  <pre><code>claustre app</code></pre>
  <p>
    This locates the <code>claustre-app</code> binary (installed alongside the
    main <code>claustre</code> binary) and launches the desktop window.
  </p>

  <h2>Features</h2>
  <p>
    The desktop app mirrors the TUI dashboard capabilities:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Project management</strong> &mdash; add, remove, and browse projects</li>
    <li><strong>Task management</strong> &mdash; create, edit, reorder, launch, kill, and delete tasks with full field support (title, description, mode, base branch, push mode, review loop)</li>
    <li><strong>Subtasks</strong> &mdash; add and manage ordered sub-steps for tasks</li>
    <li><strong>Task launching</strong> &mdash; launch tasks to create sessions with git worktrees and start Claude</li>
    <li><strong>Split pane sessions</strong> &mdash; each session opens with a Shell pane (left) + Claude pane (right), with dynamic splitting and focus switching</li>
    <li><strong>Session monitoring</strong> &mdash; view active sessions with status indicators, CI badges, and git diff stats</li>
    <li><strong>Task filter</strong> &mdash; filter tasks by title with live results (<code>/</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Command palette</strong> &mdash; searchable action menu (<code>Ctrl+P</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Help overlay</strong> &mdash; keyboard shortcuts reference (<code>?</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Skills panel</strong> &mdash; find, install, remove, and update Claude Code skills (<code>i</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Configure wizard</strong> &mdash; check and apply recommended Claude Code permissions (<code>c</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Statistics</strong> &mdash; view project-level stats and external Claude sessions</li>
    <li><strong>Rate limits</strong> &mdash; monitor current API usage in the title bar</li>
    <li><strong>Status bar</strong> &mdash; attention counter for tasks needing action</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-refresh</strong> &mdash; the UI polls the database every 2 seconds to reflect changes from hooks and other processes</li>
  </ul>

